{{Politics of New Caledonia}} '''Vice President of the Government of New Caledonia''' ({{lang-fr|Vice-Président du gouvernement de la Nouvelle-Calédonie}}) is a political position in the [[Government of New Caledonia]]. According to the [[Nouméa Accord]], Vice President in the collegial government system needs to come from a pro-independence party if the [[President of the Government of New Caledonia|President]] comes from an anti-independence party.<ref name=rnzi>{{cite news |first=|last=|title=Ngaiohni elected new New Caledonia vice president|url=http://www.radionz.co.nz/international/pacific-news/184240/ngaiohni-elected-new-new-caledonia-vice-president |work=[[Radio New Zealand International]]|publisher=|date=2009-06-15 |accessdate=2018-02-08}}</ref>
